  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ByteArray
    Abstraction of a byte[] so that different implementations can be plugged in, for example off-heap, dynamically growing, or other implementations.
    IntArray
    Abstraction of a int[] so that different implementations can be plugged in, for example off-heap, dynamically growing, or other implementations.
    LongArray
    Abstraction of a long[] so that different implementations can be plugged in, for example off-heap, dynamically growing, or other implementations.
